This is a command-line application for using Essential Realities P5 glove as an Open Sound Control client on a an OSX Macintosh. Use at your own risk.\
\
This project was made possible by a Arts Innovation Grant from Arts Victoria(Australia).\
\
\
\
\
The package installer will install two things on your machine;\
\
	1/ The P5 driver which enables the glove. PLEASE NOTE this will also 		the disable mouse mode of the glove. Please let me know if this is an 		intolerable inconvenience, I have found that using the glove as a point is 		intolerable so I disabled it.\
\
	2/ The p5osc application which is the OSC client app. It is a command line 	tool as this seems the most lightweight option in terms of CPU usage etc. 		The app will be installed into /Applications/p5osc.\
\
\
Once installation has finished, package maker will restart your machine.\
\
\
On restart, start the application "Terminal" in the Application/Utilities folder.\
\
